CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 7, 1958, pg. A12 reads: "Baltimore Gays got a thrill out of having one of their members, Mae Allen, elected national president. Left to right, are Lillian Parrott, Ruth Lightston, Mae Wright Allen, Dukye Woods, Berne Milai of Pittsburgh's host chapter, and Edna Campbell."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of six Gay Northeasterner members, from left: Lillian Parrott, Ruth Lightston, Mae Wright Allen, Dukye Woods, Berne Milai, and Edna Campbell, standing in Penn Sheraton Hotel for grand ball
